text.tspan: Share vs. intensity of multidimensional poverty, 2000 to 2021
Multidimensional poverty is defined as being deprived in a range of health, education and living standards
indicators. The intensity is the share of indicators in which the multidimensionally poor are deprived on average.
Data source: Alkire, Kanagaratnam and Suppa (2023), The global Multidimensional Poverty Index (MPI) 2023; HYDE (2023);
Note: This data aims to provide estimates that are comparable over time within individual countries. A separate dataset provides more
complete data to be used for comparisons across countries at a point in time.
